ints. The Java constant names from `java.sql.Connection` would be helpful for API reference but aren't critical since the string equivalents are documented. I don't see any significant omissions or fabrications in the knowledge file overall.\n\nNow examining the structure more carefully — the knowledge file title references the JNDI configuration section specifically, but the source actually covers both DataSource and JNDI approaches. That said, the title field is just metadata and doesn't need to match the source structure exactly. The source has multiple h2 sections covering configuration details and examples, though the organization is a bit fragmented. Looking at the RST heading syntax more carefully—the `====` underline indicates an h1 level heading, while `----` marks h2. So the source actually has the JNDI config example as a top-level heading, not nested under the first 設定内容詳細 section. This means the knowledge file's approach of grouping them together in s2 is a reasonable organizational choice, even though they're technically at different heading levels in the source. Looking at the RST structure more carefully, the `===` underline marks the JNDI section as a top-level heading while the `---` underlines indicate subsections, so the second 設定内容詳細 is indeed nested under the JNDI example. The merge in s2 makes sense structurally. The main gap I'm finding is that s1 is missing the `sql` property name from section d about BasicDbAccessExceptionFactory—that's a minor omission but worth noting. The full class name `nablarch.core.db.connection.exception.BasicDbAccessExceptionFactory` is correctly referenced in both the source documentation and the knowledge file, so that checks out. The knowledge file title mentions only JNDI configuration, but the actual content covers both DataSource and JNDI approaches, which is fine since the title is just metadata.\n\nThe key discrepancy I'm finding is that the knowledge file lists the isolationLevel values as simple string na